I89. Resident Advisory Committees

I19(a) Establishment and purpose

I11(1) A Resident Advisory Committee is an elected body of residents at each facility of the Retirement Home established to provide a forum for all residents to express their needs, ideas, and interests through elected representatives of their respective floor or area.

I11(2) A Resident Advisory Committee_

I12(A) serves as a forum for ideas, recommendations, and representation to management of that facility of the Retirement Home to enhance the morale, safety, health, and well-being of residents; and

I12(B) provides a means to communicate policy and general information between residents and management.

I19(b) Election process

I11The election process for the Resident Advisory Committee at a facility of the Retirement Home shall be coordinated by the facility Ombudsman.

I19(c) Chairperson

I11(1) The Chairperson of a Resident Advisory Committee shall be elected at large and serve a two-year term.

I11(2) Chairpersons serve as a liaison to the Administrator and are voting members of the Advisory Council. Chairpersons shall create meeting agendas, conduct the meetings, and provide a copy of the minutes to the Administrator, who will forward the copy to the Chief Operating Officer for approval.

I19(d) Meetings

I11At a minimum, meetings of a Resident Advisory Committee shall be conducted quarterly.

