I11The Chief Operating Officer or the Administrator of a facility of the Retirement Home may recruit and train persons to provide services authorized to be accepted under subsection (a) of this section.

I19(d) Status of persons providing services

I11(1) Subject to paragraph (3), while providing services accepted under subsection (a) of this section or receiving training under subsection (c) of this section, a person shall be considered to be an employee of the Federal Government only for purposes of the following provisions of law:

I12(A) Subchapter I of chapter 81 of title 5 (relating to compensation for work-related injuries).

I12(B) Chapter 171 of title 28 (relating to claims for damages or loss).

